<H1>&nbsp;</H1>
<H1><FONT color=mediumblue>ContentWord x Transcript Representation </FONT></H1>
</CENTER>

<UL><UL><UL><UL><UL><UL><UL>
       <LI><FONT size=5>In the LSI model, content-words and transcripts are represented by an <FONT color=red> m x n </FONT> incidence matrix A .</FONT></LI>
       <BR><BR>
       <LI><FONT size=5>Each of the <FONT color=red> m </FONT> unique content-words in the transcript collection are assigned a row in the matrix .</FONT></LI>
       <BR><BR>
       <LI><FONT size=5>Each of the <FONT color=red> n </FONT> transcripts in the collection are assigned a column in the matrix.</FONT></LI>
       <BR><BR>
       <LI><FONT size=5>A non-zero element <FONT color=red> a</FONT><font color="#FF0000"><sub>ij</sub></font> <FONT color=red> </FONT> , where <FONT color=red> A =
        [a</FONT><font color="#FF0000"><sub>ij</sub></font><FONT color=red>] </FONT> indicates not only that content-word <FONT color=red> i </FONT> occurs in transcript <FONT color=red> j </FONT>, but also the number of times the content-word appears in that transcript .</FONT></LI>
</UL></UL></UL></UL></UL></UL></UL>

